258
00:23:30.008 --> 00:23:32.704
Okay. You can go back to the
hostel after rehearsal.

259
00:23:37.349 --> 00:23:39.715
Fine! At least you'll be away from
that Rehan guide.

260
00:23:46.825 --> 00:23:50.591
Brother. tell me something.
You stand here all day.

261
00:23:50.829 --> 00:23:54.424
Don't you wish you were inside
on the President's chair?

262
00:23:54.833 --> 00:23:56.095
Why should l think that?

263
00:23:56.401 --> 00:23:58.767
ln the police we regularly get promoted.

264
00:23:59.004 --> 00:24:02.201
But once you're President.
there's no scope of promotion at all!

265
00:24:03.775 --> 00:24:05.367
You're a very jolly man!

266
00:24:05.610 --> 00:24:06.872
All thanks to my grandfather.

267
00:24:07.345 --> 00:24:09.711
Grandfather?
- My grandfather worked for the British.

268
00:24:09.948 --> 00:24:12.382
All day long he would hear them say
'Jolly Good' this and 'Jolly Good' that.

269
00:24:12.651 --> 00:24:15.211
When l was born he was losing his memory.

270
00:24:15.487 --> 00:24:17.421
All he remembered was 'Jolly Good'.

271
00:24:17.656 --> 00:24:19.089
So that's what he named me. Jolly Good.

272
00:24:20.659 --> 00:24:21.591
Yes. yes have a laugh at me.

273
00:24:21.827 --> 00:24:23.260
Even the officers that pass by here say..

274
00:24:23.495 --> 00:24:26.760
..''Jolly Good..Singh'' laugh and move on.

275
00:24:27.065 --> 00:24:28.259
l think that's great.

276
00:24:28.500 --> 00:24:30.263
Thanks to you. the country
is run in good spirits!

277
00:24:39.511 --> 00:24:43.777
''l felt God himself had blessed me.

278
00:24:44.683 --> 00:24:49.120
When all she did was to address me.''

279
00:25:02.334 --> 00:25:04.427
Look. l sent Rana with Balwaan and the bus.

280
00:25:05.170 --> 00:25:06.262
No. l'm not coming today.

281
00:25:07.405 --> 00:25:09.430
So what if l didn't tell you earlier.
l'm telling you now.

282
00:25:09.841 --> 00:25:11.775
Let's go.
- You left work without permission?

283
00:25:12.511 --> 00:25:13.443
So?

284
00:25:14.513 --> 00:25:16.777
My father says that if a person
can't be loyal to their work..

285
00:25:17.082 --> 00:25:19.607
..they can't be trusted for anything.

286
00:25:21.720 --> 00:25:25.622
l've left work for you and you're
giving me a speech on loyalty?

287
00:25:25.891 --> 00:25:28.325
My mother says there is
nothing bigger than loyalty.

288
00:25:29.394 --> 00:25:31.487
lf you're done with your mother and
father's sermons can we go?

289
00:25:31.730 --> 00:25:33.163
Why am l saying all this to you ?

290
00:25:33.398 --> 00:25:34.330
Why are you saying all this to me?

291
00:25:37.235 --> 00:25:38.497
So that l go back to work?

292
00:25:38.737 --> 00:25:39.499
Yes.

293
00:25:45.410 --> 00:25:50.507
Think about it. if l go today
l won't come back tomorrow.

294
00:25:51.750 --> 00:25:55.015
l'll go back to the guest house.
you'll go back to work.

295
00:25:55.287 --> 00:25:57.847
Tomorrow you'll take the day off
and then we'll go. ok?

296
00:26:01.893 --> 00:26:06.830
You've heard what your parents
have said. Now hear me.

297
00:26:08.733 --> 00:26:11.668
lf l go today l will not come back tomorrow.

298
00:26:16.741 --> 00:26:18.834
You'll come. Let's go.

299
00:26:20.579 --> 00:26:27.007
''l don't live the life of the selfless.
nor do l grab another's wine.

300
00:26:27.786 --> 00:26:30.550
lf she has love let her come and declare it..

301
00:26:31.289 --> 00:26:35.055
..to ask her. to follow her. l decline.''

302
00:26:36.628 --> 00:26:37.390
God be with you.

303
00:26:55.981 --> 00:26:56.913
Greetings Ms. Zooni.

304
00:26:57.315 --> 00:26:58.407
Greetings Mr. Jolly

305
00:27:03.788 --> 00:27:04.345
